From: Thomas Arcila <134677+tarcila@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Enable SSE2NEON for the ANARI device library

Cycles' util/half.h takes the __ARM_NEON code path whenever the compiler
defines __ARM_NEON, but the include that pulls in <arm_neon.h> (via
util/simd.h) is guarded by __KERNEL_SSE2__, which optimization.h only
defines when WITH_SSE2NEON is set.

Cycles turns this on through add_definitions(-DWITH_SSE2NEON) and a
matching include_directories() in cmake/configure_build.cmake, but those
are scoped to the cycles/ subtree. The device/ library is a sibling
subdirectory and never inherits them, so its translation units compile
the NEON path without the intrinsics header and fail to build on ARM.

Mirror cycles' own logic on the device target using the cache variables
it already populates.
---
 device/CMakeLists.txt | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/device/CMakeLists.txt b/device/CMakeLists.txt
index e22a2a4..5e87904 100644
--- a/device/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/device/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -65,6 +65,13 @@
   target_compile_options(${PROJECT_NAME} PRIVATE -msse4.2)
 endif()

+# On ARM, cycles' util/half.h uses NEON intrinsics through the SSE2NEON path.
+# WITH_SSE2NEON is only added to the cycles/ subtree, so replicate it here.
+if(SUPPORTS_NEON_BUILD AND SSE2NEON_INCLUDE_DIR)
+  target_compile_definitions(${PROJECT_NAME} PRIVATE WITH_SSE2NEON)
+  target_include_directories(${PROJECT_NAME} SYSTEM PRIVATE ${SSE2NEON_INCLUDE_DIR})
+endif()
+
 if(ANARI_CYCLES_USE_OPTIX)
   target_compile_definitions(${PROJECT_NAME} PRIVATE WITH_OPTIX)
 endif()
